There's no satellite radio,
but there's a banjo in the closet.

07:37.156 --> 07:39.317
And watch out for live-ins.

07:39.425 --> 07:42.019
You will get some live-ins.

07:49.602 --> 07:51.832
<i>Michael was investigating his father's case...</i>

07:51.938 --> 07:55.032
<i>in the English section
of Orange County.</i>

07:55.141 --> 07:57.041
Lanes reverse!

07:57.143 --> 07:59.737
You're driving on the wrong side,
you bloomin' idiot!

07:59.846 --> 08:01.677
I need to check the records...

08:01.781 --> 08:03.646
for any British-owned
building businesses...

08:03.749 --> 08:06.309
that would have applied for license
about 10 years ago.

08:06.419 --> 08:10.685
Oh, I'm so sorry. You need
a U.K. Passport to check those files.

08:10.790 --> 08:13.588
They're for British eyes only.

08:15.695 --> 08:17.526
Don't I look kind of British?

08:17.630 --> 08:19.655
Perhaps if you're willing
to lose 20 pounds.

08:19.765 --> 08:21.665
<i>The clerk was asking for a bribe...</i>

08:21.767 --> 08:25.533
<i>- but this was lost on Michael.</i>
- You guys do go for the jugular.

08:25.638 --> 08:28.038
If you find someone with a passport,
we're here till 8:00...

08:28.140 --> 08:30.665
and do stay for the Poppins.

08:30.776 --> 08:32.676
<i>So Michael went to the local pub...</i>

08:32.778 --> 08:35.042
- Bloody Yank!
<i>- to see if he could find someone...</i>

08:35.147 --> 08:37.741
<i>- with a British passport.</i>
- Welcome to the Yellow Fang.

08:37.850 --> 08:40.284
I am Lionel, and the soup of the day is...

08:40.385 --> 08:42.581
What's the soup of the day, Mum?

08:42.688 --> 08:46.021
- Bread.
- And the soup of the day is bread...

08:46.125 --> 08:48.093
Unless you’re just here for the Poppins.

08:48.194 --> 08:51.857
<i>And that's when Michael saw
the most beautiful woman he'd ever seen.</i>

08:51.964 --> 08:53.898
<i>Not her.</i>

08:54.000 --> 08:55.900
<i>Wait for it.</i>

09:02.141 --> 09:04.132
Are you from Wee Britain?

09:04.243 --> 09:06.211
Great Britain, actually.

09:06.312 --> 09:09.247
I was wondering if you might
be willing to go somewhere with me.

09:09.348 --> 09:13.216
- I will pay you.
- You'll pay me?

09:13.319 --> 09:17.016
Not... Not for sex. You're gonna think
that I'm Jack the Ripper, right?

09:17.123 --> 09:20.490
- Didn't he kill prostitutes or...
- I'm not a prostitute.

09:20.593 --> 09:23.460
Then I shall let you live.

09:23.563 --> 09:26.726
This is my worst hello.
Let me try again.

09:26.832 --> 09:29.232
- My name is Michael.
- Rita.

09:29.335 --> 09:31.235
So I need access to these files...

09:31.337 --> 09:33.532
that are apparently
for British eyes only.

09:33.639 --> 09:38.303
Well, lucky for you,
my whole face is British.

09:41.280 --> 09:44.078
It's just across the street.
I really appreciate... Hello.

09:44.183 --> 09:46.481
- I thought you said you were open till 8:00.
- Oh, yes... GMT.

09:46.586 --> 09:49.487
Everything here is on Greenwich mean time.

09:49.589 --> 09:52.183
What a curious street.

09:52.291 --> 09:56.193
Uh... Wait, wait, Rita. I don't suppose
that you're here tomorrow morning?

09:56.295 --> 09:59.287
Oh, no. Not in the morning, no.
I'll be back at Slowbrooke.

09:59.398 --> 10:02.299
Slowbrooke... The private school.
You teach kids, huh?

10:02.401 --> 10:04.460
I like to think they teach me.

10:04.570 --> 10:07.130
- Like what? How to eat crayons, throw tantrums...
- Oh, no.

10:07.239 --> 10:10.037
Not when I'm there.
I'm very good.

10:10.142 --> 10:14.135
I didn't mean to impugn
your ability or, uh...

10:14.246 --> 10:16.646
It's turning into one of my worst good-byes.

10:16.749 --> 10:19.047
Farewell, and, uh...

10:19.151 --> 10:21.779
our paths shan't cross again.

10:21.887 --> 10:24.287
As you like it.

10:24.390 --> 10:26.153
<i>Michael would have walked away forever...</i>

10:26.258 --> 10:28.123
<i>but he was struck by
something he remembered...</i>

10:28.227 --> 10:30.821
<i>- from his childhood.</i>
- You know...

10:30.930 --> 10:33.728
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
it's the flight of the Mary Poppins.</i>

10:33.833 --> 10:36.996
<i>- Mary Poppins will take...</i>
- Well, must be the Poppins.

10:37.103 --> 10:40.197
Oh, I'm sorry.
It's wrong to laugh.

10:40.306 --> 10:43.707
No, no, it was good. I liked it.
I was just gonna ask you...

10:43.809 --> 10:45.709
Pre-schools just go half day, right?

10:45.811 --> 10:48.780
I'm not trying to pick you up, but
is there any way that I can come by...

10:48.881 --> 10:51.645
- pick you up, bring you here?
- Yeah, l... I, uh...

10:51.751 --> 10:55.312
I suppose I could sneak out at nap time.

10:55.421 --> 10:57.321
- Yes? Perfect. Great.
- Mmm.

10:57.423 --> 10:59.653
And I shall drop you
off alive, hooker or no.

11:02.361 --> 11:04.761
<i>Tobias, still hoping to be in Gob's trick...</i>

11:04.864 --> 11:09.597
<i>- ventured into a costume shop he'd stumbled upon...</i>
- Oh, look who's back.

11:09.702 --> 11:13.035
<i>- years earlier.</i>
- Are you gonna buy this time, or you just curious?

11:13.139 --> 11:15.767
I suppose I'm, uh, buy-curious.

11:15.875 --> 11:17.843
I have a big TV opportunity.

11:17.943 --> 11:20.070
This is where all the big TVs come.

11:20.179 --> 11:23.945
- Uh, let's start with the Eve Arden.
- All right.

11:24.050 --> 11:25.950
<i>Michael, meanwhile, called his sister.</i>

11:26.052 --> 11:29.215
I wanted to tell you that I got myself
a date with a beautiful woman...

11:29.321 --> 11:32.757
named Rita, and you're the chicken, not me.

11:32.858 --> 11:35.190
Cluck, cluck, cluck, cluck, cluck...

11:35.294 --> 11:39.060
Okay. That's a pretty good chicken.

11:50.409 --> 11:52.309
Watch out!

11:52.411 --> 11:55.073
Crazy Brit!

11:55.181 --> 11:57.274
What's the problem?

11:57.383 --> 11:59.283
I know what you were
doing back there.

11:59.385 --> 12:01.285
And if you've got half
a !@%$# brain...

12:01.387 --> 12:04.550
- you'll leave it alone.
- You talking about back in Wee Britain?

12:04.657 --> 12:06.557
- I was just asking a few questions.
- Yeah...

12:06.659 --> 12:08.559
A few too many, if you ask me.

12:08.661 --> 12:11.221
How would you like someone going
after some stupid person in your family?

12:11.330 --> 12:14.094
Now, back off, you !@%$# ponce!

12:16.268 --> 12:18.463
Wow.

12:18.571 --> 12:21.131
Dad was not kidding
about their breath.

12:24.310 --> 12:26.244
<i>Michael had just been threatened...</i>

12:26.345 --> 12:28.779
<i>by a foul-mouthed British man.</i>

12:28.881 --> 12:30.781
It's Michael. I'm not dressed.

12:30.883 --> 12:33.249
Gob, this is Michael.

12:33.352 --> 12:35.513
Shouldn't you be getting ready
for your "Free Bird" trick?

12:35.621 --> 12:37.589
- I couldn't get the rights to "Free Bird."
- Oh.

12:37.690 --> 12:40.318
I'm thinking about calling it "Free..."
I don't know. "Chicken."

12:40.426 --> 12:43.259
I thought you were investigating Dad's
sinister British connection.

12:43.362 --> 12:45.262
Yeah. I, uh, tried, but, uh...

12:45.364 --> 12:47.264
when I was leaving...

12:47.366 --> 12:50.494
one of those British guys
came after me and told me to back off.

12:50.603 --> 12:52.696
Can't believe it, but Dad
may have been telling the truth.

12:52.805 --> 12:55.603
- This might be dangerous.
- So you came back here to hide like a child.

12:55.708 --> 12:59.439
- What are you doing locked in my office, exactly?
- Hiding from a child.

12:59.545 --> 13:01.604
- Big difference.
- Gob, Steve Holt is your son.

13:01.714 --> 13:04.274
- He probably just feels a connection.
- He doesn't know what he feels.

13:04.383 --> 13:06.283
I'm tried of being told.

13:07.820 --> 13:10.618
My God.
What is this feeling?

13:10.723 --> 13:12.691
You know, the feeling that you're...

13:12.792 --> 13:15.852
that you're feeling, it's just
what many of us call a feeling.

13:15.961 --> 13:17.861
It's not like envy...

13:17.963 --> 13:20.864
- Or even hungry.
- Could it be love?

13:20.966 --> 13:24.163
I know what an erection feels like, Michael.
No. It's the opposite.

13:24.270 --> 13:26.465
It's like my heart is getting hard.

13:27.506 --> 13:30.202
Maybe I am ready to be a father.

13:30.309 --> 13:32.368
- Hey, Dad?
- Whoa!

13:32.478 --> 13:34.469
It's my son, Gob.

13:34.580 --> 13:38.175
You know, and what is it with the fathers
in this family always trying to deceive their...

13:38.284 --> 13:40.650
<i>And that's when
Michael realized that the man...</i>

13:40.753 --> 13:43.278
<i>who threatened him
must have been hired by George Sr.</i>

13:43.389 --> 13:45.357
I'm the patsy.

13:46.692 --> 13:48.626
Well, I gotta go.
George Michael?

