I'm sorry, but we're gonna talk
about that girl later, okay?

13:51.697 --> 13:53.597
Now all I have to do
is find that look-alike, Michael.

13:53.699 --> 13:55.599
Michael?

13:57.136 --> 13:59.400
Hey!

14:00.439 --> 14:02.669
That's a woman's wig.

14:02.775 --> 14:04.675
I was told it was a bob.

14:07.112 --> 14:09.774
<i>- And Michael confronted his father.</i>
- Find out anything?

14:09.882 --> 14:11.782
Yeah, I found out no matter
how many times I promise myself...

14:11.884 --> 14:13.784
I'm not gonna fall for it,
I always end up...

14:13.886 --> 14:15.911
- getting hustled by you.
- What are you talking about?

14:16.021 --> 14:18.785
The guy that you hired to threaten me
after I looked into the British connection.

14:18.891 --> 14:20.756
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Somebody threatened you?

14:20.860 --> 14:22.885
It's a wonderful performance.
You're a regular Brad Garrett.

14:22.995 --> 14:24.860
But I don't watch TV
at 3:00 in the afternoon...

14:24.964 --> 14:26.693
and you can forget
about pleading not guilty.

14:26.799 --> 14:29.359
- Guilty. We gotta plead guilty.
- What?

14:29.468 --> 14:31.800
Michael, I didn't hire anyone,
I... I swear.

14:31.904 --> 14:34.771
If someone came after you,
they're for real.

14:34.874 --> 14:37.775
- Come on. You serious?
- I told you. These are bad guys.

14:37.877 --> 14:40.107
They do not want
this information out.

14:40.212 --> 14:42.373
He said he was gonna come
after somebody stupid in our family.

14:42.481 --> 14:45.473
- That could be Buster.
- Could be Gob.

14:45.584 --> 14:48.451
- You're not guilty.
- We have to plead guilty.

14:48.554 --> 14:51.387
- We gotta plead guilty.
- We gotta throw ourselves on the mercy of the court.

14:51.490 --> 14:54.755
- We gotta get Andy Griffith.
- In the suit.

14:54.860 --> 14:56.885
<i>And Michael went to cancel with Rita.</i>

14:56.996 --> 14:59.430
Sorry. I just wanted
to let you know...

14:59.531 --> 15:01.965
that I'm not gonna be needing
your passport after all.

15:02.067 --> 15:04.399
We're just gonna go to court, plead guilty.
That'll be that.

15:04.503 --> 15:08.132
- So it's bye-bye to Rita, then?
- Yes, I'll shake your hand good-bye...

15:08.240 --> 15:11.801
but, actually, I was wondering
if you might want to...

15:11.911 --> 15:15.142
I wouldn't. I'll make you blue.

15:15.247 --> 15:18.182
<i>Rita was just talking about the finger paint...</i>

15:18.284 --> 15:20.514
<i>- but Michael didn't know that.</i>
- I was just wondering...

15:20.619 --> 15:24.453
if you might want to bid me fair morrow.

15:24.556 --> 15:28.253
<i>Michael was filled with self-loathing.</i>

15:28.360 --> 15:32.456
<i>Had he been Jack the Ripper,
he would have soothed himself...</i>

15:32.564 --> 15:35.032
<i>in a most unsavory way.</i>

15:35.134 --> 15:37.193
<i>But instead he just
sat in his car...</i>

15:37.303 --> 15:40.500
<i>and ate a whole thing
of candy beans.</i>

15:40.606 --> 15:44.235
<i>And back at the penthouse,
Gob had been called to see his father.</i>

15:44.343 --> 15:46.243
New plan, right?

15:46.345 --> 15:49.337
<i>You put me in the trick.
You make me the guy in the cage.</i>

15:49.448 --> 15:51.507
Okay, I just gotta say
I'm really blown away by this.

15:51.617 --> 15:54.848
You really want to be part of my world.

15:54.954 --> 15:59.448
- I do.
- God, I feel like my heart is straining through my shirt.

15:59.558 --> 16:01.719
They take the ankle monitor off
when I get to court.

16:01.827 --> 16:04.694
So, you make me disappear,
you put Tobias in the cage...

16:04.797 --> 16:07.698
and by the time they realize
that that guy is not me...

16:07.800 --> 16:10.394
I'm running through
the storm drains to freedom.

16:10.502 --> 16:12.993
Where every day it rains...

16:13.105 --> 16:15.539
pennies from heaven!

16:20.145 --> 16:22.375
It was a... bird day...

16:22.481 --> 16:25.382
Gob, I know you're looking
for a twin for your illusion...

16:25.484 --> 16:28.317
and there's somebody
I'd like to put in a plug for.

16:28.420 --> 16:32.379
Uh... Correction.
Make that 4,000 plugs.

16:32.491 --> 16:34.220
- Oh, God!
- Oh, come on.

16:34.326 --> 16:35.725
Mr. Gay, he's bleeding.
Mr. Gay...

16:35.828 --> 16:38.388
No, no, no, no...
I was scared too...

16:38.497 --> 16:41.489
but I realized it was
of being a leading man.

16:41.600 --> 16:45.195
Oh, I can just taste those meaty
leading-man parts in my mouth.

16:45.304 --> 16:48.273
All right, listen to me. The trick
has changed. We want you to play me now.

16:48.374 --> 16:51.775
Oh, but that would mean
I'd have to sh...

16:51.877 --> 16:54.573
Shave my very...
tender head. I see.

16:54.680 --> 16:57.376
Okay. Well, perhaps
I jumped the gun...

16:57.483 --> 16:59.383
on those new head shots.

17:01.353 --> 17:03.844
<i>And later that day,
Michael arrived at the courthouse.</i>

17:03.956 --> 17:05.981
I can't believe you're
just giving up like this.

17:06.090 --> 17:08.059
Well, the guy threatened our family.
We have to plead guilty.

17:08.160 --> 17:10.127
No, I'm talking about that girl
you said you have a date with.

17:10.229 --> 17:12.196
All right, so I lied.
It wasn't a date.

17:12.297 --> 17:14.196
But you could have
made one with her.

17:14.299 --> 17:16.460
I think that Poppins knocked
the courage out of you.

17:16.568 --> 17:18.468
I guess I'm just not in her league.

17:18.569 --> 17:20.560
- How did you hear about the Poppins?
- It was on the news.

17:20.672 --> 17:23.698
An unlicensed Mary Poppins
takes down another tourist.

17:23.809 --> 17:28.371
Is this the work of the Itsy Bitsy IRA?

17:28.480 --> 17:30.380
I don't want to talk about this.

17:30.482 --> 17:32.541
Dad, we're gonna go in there,
Andy Griffith's gonna whisper something.

17:32.651 --> 17:34.551
We're gonna plead guilty.
Nice and simple.

17:34.653 --> 17:37.121
- You didn't hear. We lost Andy.
- What are you talking about?

17:37.222 --> 17:40.214
- He didn't like his trailer.
- He thought we were making fun of him.

17:40.325 --> 17:42.486
<i>No one was making fun of Andy Griffith.</i>

17:42.594 --> 17:44.562
<i>I can't emphasize that enough.</i>

17:46.732 --> 17:48.632
Oh, God. Don't look now...

17:48.734 --> 17:50.634
but Gob's doing his magic show.

17:50.736 --> 17:53.762
Oh, boy, a stupid magic show.
We gotta watch this.

17:53.872 --> 17:57.968
- A big turnout.
- A lot of people are probably here for the free chicken.

17:58.077 --> 17:59.977
Gather round, humans...

18:00.079 --> 18:01.979
and I will show you the plight...

18:02.081 --> 18:04.015
of an innocent man
who yearns to be...

18:04.116 --> 18:07.313
free as a bird!

18:07.419 --> 18:10.820
I've gotta start labeling these suits.

18:10.923 --> 18:13.687
Who shall I send on this journey...

18:13.792 --> 18:16.283
to that dangling cage?

18:16.395 --> 18:20.331
Oh, pick me. Look, could I be
in this stupid trick?

18:20.432 --> 18:22.491
- Please?
- Steve Holt, what are you doing here?

18:22.601 --> 18:24.967
I just came to see the magic show.

18:25.070 --> 18:26.970
I didn't know it was you.

18:27.072 --> 18:30.200
- Do you like magic?
- No.

18:30.309 --> 18:32.675
- I love it.
<i>-  And at that moment...</i>

18:32.778 --> 18:36.009
<i>Gob chose to show his own son
what he was capable of.</i>

18:36.115 --> 18:38.379
I've decided I will be
performing the feat...

18:38.484 --> 18:40.384
myself.

18:40.486 --> 18:44.320
<i>- Wait. We're back to hair?</i>
-  Fortunately for Tobias, however...

18:44.423 --> 18:48.519
<i>- he'd found it too painful
to part with his new hair.</i>

18:48.627 --> 18:53.030
- Boy. Did I catch a break.
<i>- So he opted to wear a bald cap.</i>

18:53.132 --> 18:55.123
This chicken...

18:55.234 --> 18:57.862
shall be wrongly cooped.

19:02.307 --> 19:04.707
-  Is that a chicken?
-  Oh, my God.

19:04.810 --> 19:08.007
- Dad, are you all right?
- I fooled his own son.

19:08.113 --> 19:11.708
I am a leading man.

19:11.817 --> 19:14.012
<i>And Gob himself
was running through the storm drains...</i>

19:14.119 --> 19:16.212
I'm sorry, Steve.

19:16.321 --> 19:18.152
<i>- free as a chicken.</i>
- I need to be a father.

19:19.257 --> 19:22.193
<i>And George Sr. needed to escape too.</i>

19:22.294 --> 19:24.694
I got him.

19:26.698 --> 19:28.598
Keeps him out of the kitchen.

19:28.700 --> 19:31.601
<i>And Michael,
seeing what a life of cowardice leads to...</i>

19:31.703 --> 19:33.830
<i>decided he'd had enough of it.</i>

19:33.939 --> 19:36.737
<i>And soon George Sr. came to,
and it was time...</i>

19:36.842 --> 19:38.742
<i>- to render a plea.</i>
- Oh, no.

19:38.844 --> 19:41.074
Prosecution's got that stud from L.A. Law.

19:41.180 --> 19:44.047
-  It's Harry Hamlin.
- I love my trailer.

19:44.149 --> 19:46.242
In the matter of The People v. Bluth...

19:46.351 --> 19:50.754
- how do you plead?
- We plead... not guilty.

19:50.790 --> 19:53.016
Order in the court!

19:53.125 --> 19:55.025
- Who let a flashbulb camera in?
- What are you doing?

19:55.127 --> 19:58.187
I'm tired of the cowardice. You're not guilty.
We're gonna fight this.

19:58.297 --> 20:00.561
They don't have a !@%$# prayer.

20:00.666 --> 20:04.033
Send the check to my accountant.

20:04.136 --> 20:07.731
- This is where Andy could have helped us.
-  I'm proud of you.

20:07.839 --> 20:09.739
It's about time I showed a little courage.

20:09.841 --> 20:11.775
I just hope those Brits
aren't as dangerous as Dad said.

20:11.877 --> 20:13.777
Well, they're not gonna
get any closer to us.

20:13.879 --> 20:17.110
If they do, we're gonna see them coming.
Oh, my God. That's Rita.

20:17.216 --> 20:20.617
I told her I was coming here and she came.

20:20.719 --> 20:22.448
- That's Rita?
- Yeah.

20:24.389 --> 20:27.790
Wow. She is way out of his league.

20:27.893 --> 20:30.623
I'm glad you're here.

20:30.729 --> 20:33.323
I wanna call you sometime
and take you out.

20:33.432 --> 20:35.400
Oh.

20:35.500 --> 20:37.491
I'd really like that.

20:41.206 --> 20:43.800
<i>And then, just to prove
to himself he wasn't a coward...</i>

20:43.909 --> 20:46.776
<i>he went one step further.</i>

20:50.048 --> 20:53.484
<i>And Rita was happy
to be in Michael's life as well.</i>

20:55.721 --> 20:59.487
<i>For you see, Rita
had a secret of her own.</i>

